PN,37901
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1777986670
OL,3,CPub-goer who killed man with punch
OL,4,Ctells court it was 'self-defence'
OL,6,FA pub regular who punched a 66-year-
OL,7,Fold man at a Christmas party claims he
OL,8,Facted in self-defence.
OL,10,FNathan Gothard, 37, is accused of
OL,11,Fkilling David Darke by punching him,
OL,12,Fcausing his skull to crack when he
OL,13,Ffell to the ground.
OL,15,FIt happened outside the Crown Inn in
OL,16,FAppleby Magna, Leicestershire, days
OL,17,Fbefore Christmas last year.
OL,19,FGothard who lives near the pub, is on
OL,20,Ftrial for murder and manslaughter.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1777986670
OL,3,CPub-goer who killed man with punch
OL,4,Ctells court it was 'self-defence'
OL,6,FHe claimed he was acting in self-
OL,7,Fdefence after Mr Darke grabbed him and
OL,8,Fthreatened to kill him.
OL,10,FHe told the court he felt "ridiculed"
OL,11,Fby a group of people inside the bar on
OL,12,Fthe evening of December 21.
OL,14,FGothard's defence barrister said in a
OL,15,Fclosing statement to the jury: "Oaf,
OL,16,Faggressor, murderer ` that's what the
OL,17,Fprosecution say Nathan Gothard is.
OL,26,@rD@[OUrD@eO]wD@`OU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1777986670
OL,3,CPub-goer who killed man with punch
OL,4,Ctells court it was 'self-defence'
OL,6,F"Nathan Gothard did not know David
OL,7,FDarke, had no beef, no bad blood with
OL,8,FDavid Darke. Had no reason, you may
OL,9,Fthink, to want him harmed, to want him
OL,10,Fdead.
OL,12,F"We have threats made by David Darke
OL,13,F'I'm going to bury you'. Those threats
OL,14,Fare confirmed by witnesses.
OL,16,F"Not a single threat was made by
OL,17,FNathan Gothard."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUxD@AOUyD@PO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1777986670
OL,3,CPub-goer who killed man with punch
OL,4,Ctells court it was 'self-defence'
OL,6,FMr Bhatia added: "Who was the
OL,7,Faggressor inside the pub? We submit,
OL,8,Fon the evidence, it was not him. He
OL,9,Fmay have been acting like a prat, he
OL,10,Fmay have been acting like an oaf, but
OL,11,Fhe was not the aggressor."
OL,13,FBut prosecutors accused Gothard of
OL,14,Fcreating a "menacing, threatening,
OL,15,Fargumentative and disputing"
OL,16,Fatmosphere.
OL,18,FThe prosecutor said: "David Darke is
OL,19,Fdead because this oaf decided to hit
OL,20,Fhim rather than walk round him.
OL,26,@nD@ROUsD@ZO]vD@LOUwD@\O]zD@VOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1777986670
OL,3,CPub-goer who killed man with punch
OL,4,Ctells court it was 'self-defence'
OL,6,F"He did that having behaved boorishly,
OL,7,Fodiously, and with contempt for
OL,8,Feveryone except his own sense of
OL,9,Fdignity and pride that night.
OL,11,F"That's the reality of this case."
OL,13,FHe continued: "Who was the aggressor
OL,14,Fin the pub? He was. He would have you
OL,15,Fbelieve no, no, he was the one being
OL,16,Foffended, he was the one being
OL,17,Finsulted. What absolute nonsense."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUsD@bO]uD@OOUyD@bO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1777986670
OL,3,CPub-goer who killed man with punch
OL,4,Ctells court it was 'self-defence'
OL,6,FProsecutors said Gothard had made a
OL,7,Fwoman inside the bar "very, very
OL,8,Funcomfortable" and created a
OL,9,F"menacing, threatening, argumentative
OL,10,Fand disputing" atmosphere.
OL,12,FThere were audible cries from the
OL,13,Fpublic gallery when Mr Joyce said:
OL,14,F"(Mr Darke's) sin that night was
OL,15,Fstanding up to the oaf on behalf of
OL,16,Fthis group and for that he ended up
OL,17,Fdead at the hands of the oaf.
OL,19,F"That was his sin ` having the courage
OL,20,Fto stand up to him and being punched
OL,21,Fso hard he didn't see Christmas."
OL,26,@oD@VOUpD@NO]qD@AOUrD@NO]vD@AOU{D@AOU}D@
OL,26,AaO]
